{"PageNumber":16,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":1620,"Width":2880,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Hash Function: collision resistance","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":302},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":179},"RightBottom":{"X":2031,"Y":302},"RightTop":{"X":2031,"Y":179}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● A hash function, $H$, is a mapping of input strings to (smaller) output strings","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":521},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":441},"RightBottom":{"X":2621,"Y":521},"RightTop":{"X":2621,"Y":441}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● We say that $H$ has weak collision resistance if, given any message, $M$, it is computationally difficult to find another message, $M' \\neq M$, such that","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":718},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":555},"RightBottom":{"X":2587,"Y":718},"RightTop":{"X":2587,"Y":555}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"formula","Text":"$$ \\bullet H(M') = H(M) $$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":323,"Y":807},"LeftTop":{"X":323,"Y":733},"RightBottom":{"X":738,"Y":807},"RightTop":{"X":738,"Y":733}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Hash function $H$ has strong collision resistance if it is computationally difficult to compute two distinct messages, $M_1$ and $M_2$, such that","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":1007},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":838},"RightBottom":{"X":2731,"Y":1007},"RightTop":{"X":2731,"Y":838}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"formula","Text":"$$ \\bullet H(M_1) = H(M_2) $$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":323,"Y":1097},"LeftTop":{"X":323,"Y":1018},"RightBottom":{"X":764,"Y":1097},"RightTop":{"X":764,"Y":1018}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● That is, in weak collision resistance, we are trying to avoid a collision with a specific message, and in strong collision resistance we are trying to avoid collisions in general","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":1369},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":1122},"RightBottom":{"X":2639,"Y":1369},"RightTop":{"X":2639,"Y":1122}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":7,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● It is usually a challenge to prove that real-world cryptographic hash functions have strong collision resistance","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":1572},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":1408},"RightBottom":{"X":2708,"Y":1572},"RightTop":{"X":2708,"Y":1408}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}